	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok everyone.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Epic Monk weapon CHANGES the damage/delay ratio of the fists.  They are EPIC weapons, they will do that.  They change your fists from the 14/28 (human) or 14/29 (Iksar) to 9/14 for all.  The haste then might drop the delay down to 10, don't know, don't care or have time to figure it out all the way.  The end result is that the monk's fists have now been coded to be 9 damage 14 delay weapons when these gloves are equipped.<br>These gloves were made to make the Monk's main weapon once again become something that you would use in greater amount.  The One hand blunt weapons that were coming out were outshining the fists, look at the Knuckle Dusters at 14/28.  Thus the Epic makes the fists 9/14, which are sweet for ratio, but you still have to have some help for those damage shields or a nice Two hand blunt staff for the longer delay :P<br><br>Roshambo Yaforit<br>Mystic Dragon Slayers<br>Solesek Ro<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
